==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: evasive
<hw>e*va"sive</hw> <pr>(⟦esl⟧*v⟦amac⟧"s⟦icr⟧v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧vasif</ets>. See <er>Evade</er>.]</ety>
<def>Tending to evade, or marked by evasion; elusive; shuffling;
avoiding by artifice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thus he, though conscious of the ethereal guest,⟦br⟧
Answered <qex>evasive</qex> of the sly request.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Stammered out a few <qex>evasive</qex> phrases.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>E*va"sive*ly</wf> , <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>E*va"sive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>evasiveness</ent>⟦br⟧
